WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.280
Oxford Bookworms, Stage 1. The Wizard of Oz, by L. Frank Baum,

00:08.240 --> 00:13.440
retold by Rosemary Border, read by Jennifer J. Myers.

00:23.680 --> 00:26.240
Chapter 1 The Cyclone

00:30.960 --> 00:41.520
Dorothy lived in a small house in Kansas with Uncle Henry, Ant M, and a little black dog called

00:41.520 --> 00:50.800
Toto. There were no trees and no hills in Kansas, and it was often very windy.

00:50.960 --> 00:58.080
Sometimes the wind came very fast and very suddenly.

00:59.760 --> 01:07.920
That was a cyclone, and it could blow trees and people and buildings away.

01:10.160 --> 01:18.800
There were cellars under all the houses, and when a cyclone came, people went down

01:18.800 --> 01:28.960
into their cellars and stayed there. One day, Uncle Henry came out and looked up at the sky.

01:30.400 --> 01:33.840
Then he ran quickly back into the house.

01:35.360 --> 01:42.480
There's a cyclone coming. He called to Ant M and Dorothy. We must go down into the cellar.

01:42.480 --> 01:51.200
They ran to the door of the cellar, but Toto was afraid, and he ran under the bed.

01:52.400 --> 01:54.080
Dorothy ran after him.

01:55.040 --> 02:02.000
Quick! shouted Ant M from the cellar. Leave the dog and come down into the cellar.

02:03.840 --> 02:07.840
Dorothy picked up Toto and ran to the cellar door.

02:08.640 --> 02:19.920
But before she got there, the cyclone hit the house, and then a very strange thing happened.

02:21.440 --> 02:31.920
The house moved, and then it went slowly up, up, up into the sky.

02:32.400 --> 02:41.360
Ant M and Uncle Henry were down in the cellar under the ground, but the house,

02:42.320 --> 02:47.840
Dorothy and Toto went up to the top of the cyclone.

02:49.920 --> 02:58.960
Dorothy looked through the open cellar door and saw hills and houses a long way down.

02:59.120 --> 03:03.520
She closed the cellar door quickly.

03:05.600 --> 03:13.840
The wind blew the house along for many hours. At first, Dorothy was afraid.

03:16.240 --> 03:22.800
But we can't do anything about it, she said to Toto. So let's wait and see.

03:22.960 --> 03:30.560
And after two or three hours, she and Toto went to sleep.

03:32.480 --> 03:40.480
When Dorothy opened her eyes again, the house was on the ground, and everything was quiet.

03:41.920 --> 03:46.880
She picked up Toto, opened the door, and went out.

03:46.960 --> 03:56.800
They saw tall trees and beautiful flowers, and little houses with blue doors.

03:58.480 --> 04:06.480
Dorothy gave a little cry. This is in Kansas, Toto, and who are these people?

04:07.440 --> 04:15.280
There were three very short men in blue hats, coats, and trousers,

04:16.400 --> 04:20.560
and a little old woman in a beautiful white dress.

04:22.240 --> 04:31.920
The woman walked up to Dorothy and said, thank you, thank you, now the people are free.

04:32.480 --> 04:40.560
Why are you thanking me? Dorothy asked, you killed the witch of the East.

04:40.560 --> 04:49.760
Said the woman, she was a bad witch, and her people, the munchkins, were very afraid of her.

04:49.760 --> 04:57.200
Now she is dead, and we and the munchkins want to thank you.

04:57.600 --> 05:06.720
The little old woman and the three little men all smiled happily at Dorothy,

05:07.680 --> 05:15.520
but Dorothy did not understand. But I didn't kill anybody, she said.

05:16.880 --> 05:21.520
Your house fell on the witch, laughed the little woman.

05:22.480 --> 05:33.840
Look, you can see her feet. Dorothy looked and saw two feet with red shoes under the house.

05:35.520 --> 05:39.200
Suddenly, one of the munchkins gave a shout.

05:40.240 --> 05:44.480
Look, her feet are disappearing in the hot sun.

05:44.480 --> 05:50.880
A second later, there were only the red shoes.

05:52.480 --> 05:59.520
Good, said the little woman, she picked up the shoes and gave them to Dorothy.

06:00.480 --> 06:11.120
They're your shoes now, you must wear them, because a witch's shoes can sometimes do wonderful things.

06:12.080 --> 06:20.160
Thank you, said Dorothy. But who are you? Are you a munchkin?

06:21.520 --> 06:31.360
No, but I'm their friend. I'm the witch of the North, and I came to see the dead witch of the East.

06:32.400 --> 06:40.960
But don't be afraid, I'm a good witch. But Aunt M says there are denny witches.

06:42.080 --> 06:51.200
Oh, yes, there are, said the witch. Here in the country of Oz, we have four witches.

06:52.080 --> 07:01.200
The witches of the North and the South are good witches, but those of the East and the West are

07:01.200 --> 07:11.200
bad witches. Now, the witch of the East is dead, so there is only one bad witch.

07:12.480 --> 07:23.600
We have a famous wizard, too. We call him the Wizard of Oz, and he lives in the Emerald City.

07:24.480 --> 07:30.240
How many witches and wizards do you have in your country?

07:32.320 --> 07:35.120
We don't have any, said Dorothy.

07:36.400 --> 07:40.320
Suddenly, she remembered Aunt M and Uncle Henry.

07:41.520 --> 07:45.520
How can I get back home to Kansas? She asked.

07:45.760 --> 07:57.920
Where is Kansas? asked the good witch. I don't know what country called Kansas, so I can't tell you the way.

07:59.840 --> 08:10.080
Dorothy began to cry. Oh, dear, what can I do? Please don't cry, said the witch.

08:11.040 --> 08:18.800
Go and see the Wizard of Oz. He's a good wizard, and perhaps he can help you.

08:19.920 --> 08:29.280
It's a long way, and you must walk there. I can't go with you, but I can give you my kiss.

08:31.680 --> 08:38.640
She gave Dorothy a little kiss. It looked like a small red flower on Dorothy's face.

08:40.560 --> 08:49.440
Now, nothing can hurt you, she said. Look, there is the road to the Emerald City.

08:50.400 --> 08:57.520
It is made of yellow bricks, so you cannot lose your way. Goodbye.

08:59.200 --> 09:02.480
Goodbye, said the three little munchkins.

09:03.280 --> 09:11.600
In the house, Dorothy found some bread and some apple, and she put them all in a bag.

09:12.960 --> 09:20.000
Then, she put on her blue and white dress. Now, I look nice, she said.

09:21.120 --> 09:29.600
She looked down at her old shoes. Then, she remembered the bad witch's red shoes, and put them on.

09:30.560 --> 09:39.360
She picked up her bag of food. Come on, Toto, she called. We're going to find the Wizard of Oz.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.960
Chapter 2, The Yellow Brick Road

09:52.960 --> 10:03.520
Dorothy and Toto walked along the Yellow Brick Road for a long time.

10:04.640 --> 10:13.360
When they were tired, they stopped in a field by the road. Not far away, there was a scarecrow,

10:14.160 --> 10:17.680
and Dorothy and Toto walked across to look at it.

10:18.080 --> 10:22.480
Good day, said the scarecrow.

10:23.680 --> 10:27.280
Oh, said Dorothy, you can speak.

10:28.640 --> 10:39.440
Of course I can speak, said the scarecrow, but I can't move up here on this pole. I'd like to get

10:39.520 --> 10:41.760
down. Can you help me?

10:43.680 --> 10:48.000
Carefully, Dorothy took the scarecrow off his pole.

10:49.200 --> 10:58.480
Thank you very much, said the scarecrow. He moved his arms and legs, and straw went everywhere.

10:59.360 --> 11:04.080
Who are you? He asked, and where are you going?

11:05.600 --> 11:15.520
I'm Dorothy, and I'm going to the Emerald City. I want to go home to Kansas, but I don't know the way.

11:16.560 --> 11:19.840
I'm going to ask the Wizard of Oz for help.

11:20.720 --> 11:28.400
Where is the Emerald City? asked the scarecrow, and who is the Wizard of Oz?

11:29.360 --> 11:37.680
I don't know anything, you see, because I have no brains in my head, only straw.

11:39.280 --> 11:43.680
Oh, dear, said Dorothy, I'm very sorry.

11:44.560 --> 11:50.000
I would very much like to have some brains, the scarecrow said.

11:51.040 --> 11:53.920
Can I go to the Emerald City with you?

11:54.960 --> 12:00.320
Perhaps the Wizard of Oz can give me some brains. What do you think?

12:02.000 --> 12:10.080
I don't know, said Dorothy, but yes, please, come with me. He's a famous wizard,

12:10.720 --> 12:16.640
so perhaps he can help you. She felt very sorry for the scarecrow.

12:17.760 --> 12:22.960
Don't be afraid of Toto, she said. He never hurts people.

12:24.320 --> 12:29.840
Nothing can hurt me, said the scarecrow. I'm not afraid of anything.

12:30.800 --> 12:36.000
Well, that's not true. I am afraid of fire, of course.

12:36.800 --> 12:40.800
Dorothy walked along the road with her new friend.

12:41.520 --> 12:50.960
Soon, she began to feel hungry, so she sat down, and she and Toto ate some bread and apples.

12:51.840 --> 12:55.440
Would you like some scarecrow? said Dorothy.

12:55.440 --> 13:01.840
No, thank you, said the scarecrow. I don't need to eat or drink.

13:02.240 --> 13:05.600
You can't eat when you're made of straw.

13:06.960 --> 13:09.680
Now, tell me about your home.

13:11.600 --> 13:18.160
So Dorothy told him about Kansas, an Uncle Henry in Ant M, and the cyclone.

13:19.680 --> 13:24.720
But why do you want to leave this beautiful country, ask the scarecrow?

13:25.680 --> 13:34.960
Kansas, you say, has no trees, no green hills, no gardens. I don't understand.

13:36.880 --> 13:40.720
That's because you have no brains, said Dorothy.

13:41.680 --> 13:52.960
Kansas is my home. We say East, West, home's best, and it's true. I want to go home.

13:55.600 --> 14:00.560
They walked along the road for some hours, and then it got dark.

14:01.760 --> 14:08.320
Dorothy was tired, and soon the scarecrow saw a little house behind some trees.

14:09.680 --> 14:12.480
There was nobody there, so they went in.

14:14.000 --> 14:20.400
Dorothy and Toto slept, but the scarecrow just stood all night with his eyes open.

14:21.280 --> 14:24.480
Scarecrows don't sleep, he said.

14:26.240 --> 14:29.120
In the morning Dorothy looked for water.

14:30.080 --> 14:33.600
Why do you want water? asked the scarecrow.

14:34.960 --> 14:38.560
Toto and I are thirsty, and I need to wash.

14:40.080 --> 14:45.840
I'm sorry for you, said the scarecrow. You need a lot of things,

14:46.800 --> 14:53.040
but you have brains, and you can think, and that's wonderful.

14:55.040 --> 15:02.000
They found some water, and Dorothy washed. Then she and Toto ate some bread.

15:03.120 --> 15:11.440
Suddenly they heard a shout from the trees near the house, and they all ran out of the house to look.

15:11.440 --> 15:18.080
They saw a man by a big tree with an axe in his hand.

15:19.200 --> 15:25.040
He was made of tin. He stood very still and shouted,

15:25.600 --> 15:28.160
Help! again and again.

15:30.080 --> 15:33.440
What can I do for you, asked Dorothy?

15:34.480 --> 15:40.320
I can't move, said the tin man. Please, oil me.

15:41.200 --> 15:44.080
There's an oil can in my house.

15:45.920 --> 15:51.200
At once Dorothy ran back to the house and found the oil can.

15:52.160 --> 15:59.680
Then she came back, and with the scarecrow's help she carefully oiled the tin man.

16:00.800 --> 16:08.800
Slowly he began to move, first his head, and then his arms and legs.

16:09.680 --> 16:14.720
Thank you, he said. I feel better now.

16:15.920 --> 16:17.920
He put down his axe.

16:19.360 --> 16:27.200
I went out in the rain, you see, and water is very bad for a tin body.

16:28.240 --> 16:34.880
I was there for a long time, and nobody came to help me.

16:35.760 --> 16:42.800
We stopped at your house for the night, Dorothy said, and we heard your shouts this morning.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
Where are you going?

16:46.640 --> 16:51.760
Asked the tin man, so Dorothy told him about the Wizard of Oz.

16:52.640 --> 16:59.120
I want to go back to Kansas, and the scarecrow wants some brains, she said.

17:00.080 --> 17:02.720
The tin man was very interested.

17:03.440 --> 17:07.440
Can the wizard give me a heart, do you think?

17:07.840 --> 17:13.520
I have no heart, so I can't love or feel.

17:13.520 --> 17:17.920
I would very much like to have a heart.

17:19.120 --> 17:21.920
Come with us, said the scarecrow.

17:21.920 --> 17:28.720
Yes, said Dorothy, and then you can ask the wizard for help too.

17:28.720 --> 17:35.280
So they all walked along the yellow brick road.

17:36.640 --> 17:40.000
There were many tall trees next to the road,

17:40.880 --> 17:47.280
and sometimes the three friends heard noises from animals behind the trees.

17:48.800 --> 17:52.160
Dorothy did not like these noises very much.

17:53.040 --> 17:56.320
How far is it to the Emerald City?

17:56.880 --> 17:59.520
She asked the tin man, do you know?

18:00.960 --> 18:08.640
It's a long way, I think, said the tin man, and we must be careful because...

18:09.840 --> 18:16.880
But just then, a big lion suddenly ran out from the trees into the road.

18:17.840 --> 18:25.360
It opened its mouth, it had long yellow teeth, and began to run after Toto.

18:26.400 --> 18:28.480
Dorothy was afraid for Toto.

18:29.280 --> 18:33.760
She ran up to the lion and hid it on the nose with her bag.

18:35.120 --> 18:38.960
Don't hurt my dog, she cried angrily.

18:39.600 --> 18:41.040
He's smaller than you.

18:42.800 --> 18:44.400
I didn't hurt him.

18:45.200 --> 18:49.600
He said the lion, don't hit me again, please.

18:51.040 --> 18:54.800
Why, you're afraid, said Dorothy.

18:55.600 --> 18:59.200
Be quiet, Toto, he isn't going to hurt you.

18:59.840 --> 19:04.400
He's more afraid than you are, he's just a big coward.

19:05.280 --> 19:10.320
It's true, said the lion, I am a coward.

19:11.200 --> 19:14.080
Everyone thinks lions are brave.

19:15.120 --> 19:21.760
I make a lot of noise, but I'm not brave, I'm just a coward.

19:23.360 --> 19:26.400
And the cowardly lion began to cry.

19:27.920 --> 19:31.840
Then Dorothy told him about the Wizard of Oz.

19:32.880 --> 19:36.160
Come with us to the Emerald City, she said.

19:37.200 --> 19:39.440
I want to go back to Kansas.

19:40.320 --> 19:45.520
The scarecrow wants some brains, and the tin man wants a heart.

19:46.560 --> 19:49.600
Perhaps the Wizard of Oz can make you brave.

19:51.280 --> 19:52.720
Oh, thank you.

19:53.840 --> 19:58.560
Said the lion, I would very much like to be brave.

20:00.080 --> 20:02.960
And so the cowardly lion came with them.

20:04.240 --> 20:10.240
At first, Toto was afraid of him, but very soon he and the lion

20:10.320 --> 20:11.600
were good friends.

20:12.880 --> 20:17.520
That night, Dorothy and Toto slept under a big tree,

20:18.320 --> 20:22.720
next to the cowardly lion's big, warm body.

20:23.760 --> 20:27.200
In the morning, they ate the last of their bread.

20:28.560 --> 20:30.880
Oh, dear, said Dorothy.

20:31.840 --> 20:34.080
What are we going to eat for dinner?

20:35.200 --> 20:38.000
I can kill an animal for you.

20:38.880 --> 20:40.720
Said the cowardly lion.

20:41.920 --> 20:46.480
Oh, no, please, don't kill anything.

20:47.120 --> 20:50.880
The tin man said, he began to cry.

20:51.840 --> 20:55.040
We don't want to hurt any animals.

20:55.520 --> 21:00.240
I haven't got a heart, but I feel sorry for them.

21:01.760 --> 21:06.080
Dorothy quickly got out the oil can and oiled his face.

21:07.040 --> 21:09.040
Don't cry, she said.

21:09.760 --> 21:12.000
You know water is bad for you.

21:14.160 --> 21:18.560
They walked along the yellow road, and after an hour or two,

21:18.560 --> 21:20.640
they came to a big river.

21:21.760 --> 21:24.080
Oh, no, said Dorothy.

21:24.800 --> 21:26.400
How can we get across?

21:27.920 --> 21:29.920
The lion looked down at the river.

21:31.360 --> 21:35.120
I'm very afraid of falling, he said.

21:36.080 --> 21:39.280
But I think I can jump across.

21:41.040 --> 21:43.920
Good, said the scarecrow at once.

21:43.920 --> 21:47.600
You can carry us on your back, one at a time.

21:49.280 --> 21:52.400
So the cowardly lion jumped across the river,

21:53.120 --> 21:55.360
first with the scarecrow on his back,

21:56.160 --> 22:00.480
then with Dorothy and Toto, and last with the tin man.

22:01.920 --> 22:04.880
But soon, they came to a second river.

22:05.840 --> 22:11.120
This one was very big, and the lion could not jump across it.

22:12.320 --> 22:14.400
The scarecrow thought for a minute.

22:15.440 --> 22:20.640
Look, he said, there's a tall tree next to the river.

22:21.200 --> 22:24.320
The tin man can cut it down with his axe,

22:25.120 --> 22:27.760
and when the tree falls across the river,

22:28.320 --> 22:30.400
we can walk across the tree.

22:31.360 --> 22:34.720
Very good, said the lion,

22:34.720 --> 22:39.760
for somebody would straw in their head and not brains.

22:41.520 --> 22:44.800
So the tin man cut down the tree with his axe,

22:45.520 --> 22:49.040
and soon they were all across that river too.

22:49.040 --> 23:02.000
Chapter Three, the Emerald City

23:07.520 --> 23:08.880
It was a long day.

23:09.760 --> 23:12.800
The yellow brick road went past fields,

23:12.800 --> 23:16.640
and through trees, up hills and downhill.

23:17.440 --> 23:23.040
In the evening, they began to see small green houses by the road.

23:24.400 --> 23:29.760
Sometimes, little people in green clothes came out and looked at the friends,

23:30.640 --> 23:32.640
but they did not come near them,

23:33.200 --> 23:36.240
because they were afraid of the cowardly lion.

23:37.920 --> 23:39.600
Everything here is green,

23:40.400 --> 23:44.160
perhaps we're near the Emerald City, said Dorothy.

23:45.120 --> 23:47.120
Toto and I are hungry.

23:47.920 --> 23:50.000
Let's stop at the next house.

23:51.520 --> 23:53.520
A little woman opened the door,

23:54.240 --> 23:55.360
and Dorothy said,

23:56.160 --> 23:59.520
please, can we stay the night in your house?

24:00.800 --> 24:02.960
The little woman looked at the lion,

24:03.600 --> 24:05.120
and Dorothy said quickly,

24:05.760 --> 24:09.840
the lion is my friend, and he never hurts anybody.

24:10.640 --> 24:13.680
All right, the little woman said,

24:14.240 --> 24:15.680
you can all come in.

24:17.440 --> 24:20.240
She put a wonderful dinner on the table.

24:21.040 --> 24:23.360
Dorothy and Toto ate a lot of it,

24:24.000 --> 24:25.600
and the lion ate some of it,

24:26.320 --> 24:29.680
but the scarecrow and the tin man ate nothing.

24:31.120 --> 24:32.800
Where are you all going?

24:33.520 --> 24:34.640
asked the little woman.

24:36.000 --> 24:38.720
To the Emerald City, said Dorothy,

24:39.600 --> 24:42.240
we want to see the Wizard of Oz.

24:43.600 --> 24:46.160
That's not easy, said the woman.

24:46.880 --> 24:49.600
The wizard never goes out of his house,

24:50.320 --> 24:52.480
and nobody sees his face.

24:54.400 --> 24:56.000
Is the wizard a man?

24:56.800 --> 24:58.000
asked the scarecrow.

24:58.880 --> 25:01.520
Nobody knows, said the woman.

25:02.240 --> 25:03.200
He's a wizard,

25:03.840 --> 25:07.440
so he can be a man or an animal,

25:08.080 --> 25:09.280
or anything.

25:10.800 --> 25:13.360
How strange, said Dorothy,

25:14.000 --> 25:17.520
but we need his help, so we must see him.

25:19.360 --> 25:22.320
The next day, they thanked the woman,

25:22.320 --> 25:25.360
left the house, and began walking again.

25:26.320 --> 25:30.080
Soon, they saw a beautiful city in front of them.

25:30.960 --> 25:34.400
It was the Emerald City at last.

25:35.280 --> 25:39.200
The friends went up the yellow brick road

25:39.200 --> 25:42.320
to a big green door and stopped.

25:43.360 --> 25:45.680
Slowly, the door opened,

25:46.400 --> 25:50.000
and a little man in green clothes stood there.

25:51.440 --> 25:54.960
We want to see the wizard, please, said Dorothy.

25:56.160 --> 25:59.360
Nobody sees the wizard, he said.

26:00.080 --> 26:04.080
He is a very good and very famous wizard,

26:04.160 --> 26:06.080
but nobody can see him.

26:07.600 --> 26:10.400
We must see him, said Dorothy.

26:11.040 --> 26:12.480
Please ask him.

26:14.000 --> 26:16.560
All right, said the green man.

26:17.440 --> 26:19.360
I can take you to his house,

26:20.080 --> 26:24.160
but first, you must all put glasses on.

26:25.520 --> 26:30.800
He opened a big box, in it were lots of glasses.

26:31.760 --> 26:35.520
You must wear your glasses all the time.

26:36.080 --> 26:40.560
He said, everybody in the city must wear glasses.

26:41.120 --> 26:42.560
The wizard says this.

26:44.320 --> 26:46.400
So they all put on glasses.

26:47.040 --> 26:49.920
The green man put on some glasses too,

26:50.880 --> 26:54.320
and then he took them through the Emerald City.

26:55.680 --> 26:57.760
Everything in the city was green.

26:58.720 --> 27:05.600
Men, women, children, houses, shops, streets.

27:07.280 --> 27:11.120
The green man took them to a very big house,

27:11.920 --> 27:14.800
and they went into a long green room.

27:15.760 --> 27:17.520
Wait here, he said.

27:18.480 --> 27:20.880
After a short time, he came back.

27:21.840 --> 27:25.360
You can see the wizard, he said.

27:26.000 --> 27:30.000
But you must go to him one by one.

27:30.960 --> 27:33.840
He wants to see the little girl first.

27:35.440 --> 27:39.920
Then he went away, and a green girl came in.

27:40.880 --> 27:43.840
She took Dorothy to a tall green door.

27:45.200 --> 27:48.880
The wizard is in there, said the green girl.

27:49.520 --> 27:50.880
He's waiting for you.

27:52.160 --> 27:53.360
Dorothy went in.

27:54.000 --> 27:58.720
On a green chair was a very, very big head.

27:59.680 --> 28:05.200
There was no body or arms or legs, only a head.

28:06.400 --> 28:09.440
Its mouth opened, and the head said,

28:10.400 --> 28:13.040
I am Oz.

28:13.920 --> 28:18.800
Who are you, and what do you want?

28:20.960 --> 28:24.720
I am Dorothy, said the child bravely.

28:26.000 --> 28:30.160
Where did you get those red shoes?

28:31.680 --> 28:34.960
From the bad witch of the east, said Dorothy.

28:35.600 --> 28:38.080
My house fell on her and killed her.

28:39.600 --> 28:42.720
What is that thing on your face?

28:44.160 --> 28:44.720
A kiss.

28:45.600 --> 28:48.960
The good witch of the north kissed me, said Dorothy.

28:49.760 --> 28:52.640
I need help, and she told me about you.

28:54.240 --> 28:56.960
And what do you want?

28:58.400 --> 29:02.720
I want to go home to Kansas, answer Dorothy.

29:03.360 --> 29:04.880
But I don't know the way.

29:05.680 --> 29:07.760
Please help me to get home.

29:09.840 --> 29:15.200
The big eyes opened and closed, opened and closed.

29:16.160 --> 29:20.080
Then the mouth opened and the head spoke again.

29:21.440 --> 29:26.800
Well, it said, perhaps I can help you.

29:27.760 --> 29:32.720
But first, you must do something for me.

29:34.400 --> 29:37.520
What do you want me to do, asked Dorothy?

29:38.480 --> 29:41.440
Kill the bad witch of the west.

29:42.720 --> 29:46.880
But I don't want to kill anybody, said Dorothy.

29:48.000 --> 29:53.360
You killed her sister, and you are wearing her shoes.

29:54.400 --> 29:59.360
Go now and kill the witch of the west.

30:01.040 --> 30:03.280
The little girl began to cry.

30:04.560 --> 30:06.880
But how can I kill the witch?

30:07.520 --> 30:15.360
She said, the big eyes opened and looked at her, but the head did not answer.

30:17.440 --> 30:22.000
Dorothy went away, and then her friends went into the wizard's room.

30:22.960 --> 30:29.120
First, the scarecrow, then the tin man, and last, the lion.

30:30.960 --> 30:35.600
Later, they all met in the long green room and talked.

30:36.480 --> 30:39.280
Dorothy told her friends about the head.

30:40.640 --> 30:43.680
That's interesting, said the scarecrow.

30:44.560 --> 30:46.160
I didn't see a head.

30:46.960 --> 30:49.200
I saw a beautiful woman.

30:50.320 --> 30:53.920
I asked her for some brains, and she said,

30:54.480 --> 31:00.400
Yes, but first, you must help Dorothy to kill the witch of the west.

31:00.960 --> 31:06.880
I saw a big animal with two heads, said the tin man.

31:07.280 --> 31:08.880
I asked for a heart.

31:08.880 --> 31:19.840
The animal said, I can give you a heart, but first, you must help Dorothy to kill the witch of the west.

31:21.040 --> 31:23.040
What did you see, lion?

31:24.240 --> 31:27.120
I saw a ball of fire.

31:27.120 --> 31:30.960
A ball of fire, said the cowardly lion.

31:31.760 --> 31:37.600
I said, I'm a coward, please make me brave.

31:38.560 --> 31:46.000
And the fire said, when the witch of the west is dead, I can help you, but not before.

31:47.360 --> 31:54.960
I was angry then, said the lion, but the ball of fire got bigger and bigger,

31:55.520 --> 31:56.800
so I ran away.

31:58.560 --> 32:02.800
Oh, what are we going to do, said Dorothy?

32:03.760 --> 32:18.480
Well, said the scarecrow, we must find the witch of the west, and then we must kill her.

32:19.360 --> 32:24.560
Chapter four, the witch and the monkey.

32:29.360 --> 32:33.040
The next morning, they left the Emerald City.

32:34.080 --> 32:40.720
The green man took away their glasses and told them the way to the witch's house.

32:41.600 --> 32:49.520
Everybody is afraid of the witch of the west, he said, so be careful.

32:51.280 --> 32:53.920
The prince walked for a long time.

32:54.720 --> 33:01.360
The road was bad, and there were no houses, no fields, no trees.

33:03.040 --> 33:09.200
Now the witch of the west had a magic eye, and it could see everything.

33:10.080 --> 33:15.440
She saw the friends on the road, and she was angry.

33:16.480 --> 33:20.560
She put on her tall black hat and shouted,

33:21.280 --> 33:23.680
magic monkeys, come!

33:25.440 --> 33:30.080
In a second, 40 monkeys arrived at her tall house.

33:30.960 --> 33:33.280
What do you want, they asked?

33:33.280 --> 33:41.120
There are three people, a dog and a lion on my road.

33:41.760 --> 33:49.120
She said, kill the people and the dog, but bring the lion here to my house.

33:49.920 --> 33:52.000
He can work for me.

33:53.520 --> 33:57.760
At once, said the monkey, and the way they went.

33:59.440 --> 34:02.480
They broke the tin man's arms and legs.

34:03.280 --> 34:10.240
They took all the straw out of the scarecrow and threw his clothes up into a tall tree.

34:11.440 --> 34:18.400
Then they took the lion and carried him to a dark cellar under the witch's house.

34:20.480 --> 34:26.400
But they could not hurt Dorothy and Toto because of the good witch's kiss.

34:27.360 --> 34:34.640
So the monkeys picked them up very carefully and carried them to the witch's house.

34:36.320 --> 34:45.280
The witch saw the kiss on Dorothy's face and was afraid, but she did not tell Dorothy that.

34:47.120 --> 34:50.880
You must work for me in my house now.

34:51.840 --> 34:57.200
She said to the child, all day and every day.

34:58.240 --> 35:04.000
And remember, I am watching you all the time.

35:06.400 --> 35:12.080
Now, Dorothy did not know this, but the red shoes were magic.

35:13.360 --> 35:19.760
The witch wanted those shoes very much, but Dorothy never took them off.

35:21.040 --> 35:27.360
She took them off when she washed, of course, but the witch never went near water.

35:28.160 --> 35:32.080
She was very, very afraid of water.

35:33.440 --> 35:38.400
Then, one morning, Dorothy's left shoe fell off.

35:39.600 --> 35:42.560
The witch picked up the shoe at once.

35:43.840 --> 35:48.240
This is my shoe now, she shouted.

35:49.040 --> 35:52.960
No, it isn't, shouted Dorothy angrily.

35:53.520 --> 35:55.440
Give it back to me at once.

35:56.880 --> 36:03.840
Now, said the witch, and then she tried to take Dorothy's right shoe too.

36:05.760 --> 36:10.800
Dorothy loved her red shoes and she was very angry.

36:12.240 --> 36:14.960
There was a bucket of water near the door.

36:15.760 --> 36:20.880
Dorothy picked up the bucket and threw the water at the witch.

36:22.080 --> 36:26.080
The water hit her in the face and she cried out,

36:26.960 --> 36:33.040
Help! Help! The water is killing me, the water is.

36:34.640 --> 36:43.680
And then she disappeared. There was only her tall black hat and a long black dress.

36:45.920 --> 36:50.640
Dorothy looked and looked, but the witch was not there.

36:52.160 --> 36:55.520
Dorothy picked up her red shoe and put it on.

36:57.120 --> 37:01.360
Now, how can I help my friend? She said,

37:02.480 --> 37:04.640
Can I call the magic monkey?

37:06.720 --> 37:10.320
She picked up the witch's black hat and looked at it.

37:11.120 --> 37:15.360
Perhaps I must wear this magic hat when I speak.

37:16.640 --> 37:21.760
So she put the hat on and called, Magic Monkeys! Come!

37:23.280 --> 37:25.440
The monkeys arrived in a second.

37:26.560 --> 37:29.040
Please, can you help my friend?

37:29.920 --> 37:30.880
At Dorothy?

37:31.840 --> 37:34.320
Of course, said the monkeys.

37:35.200 --> 37:40.880
We must always help the wearer of the magic black hat.

37:42.880 --> 37:47.600
They broke open the dark cellar and the cowardly lion came out.

37:48.560 --> 37:52.320
Free at last, he said, thank you.

37:54.160 --> 37:59.600
Then the monkeys found the scarecrow's clothes and put some new straw in them.

38:00.480 --> 38:05.360
The scarecrow laughed and jumped, thank you, he said.

38:06.400 --> 38:12.640
Next, the monkeys mended the tin man and gave him a new oil can.

38:13.680 --> 38:16.080
He moved his arms and legs.

38:16.960 --> 38:21.680
I feel wonderful, he said, thank you.

38:23.280 --> 38:27.040
Dorothy told her friends about the witch and the water,

38:27.600 --> 38:29.760
and they were all very happy.

38:30.800 --> 38:35.920
Toto could not speak, but he jumped up and down very happily.

38:37.120 --> 38:42.000
Now, said Dorothy, we must go back to the Wizard of Oz.

38:43.040 --> 38:47.040
Magic Monkeys, take us to the Emerald City.

38:48.320 --> 38:52.640
Don't forget the magic black hat, said the tin man.

38:53.600 --> 38:59.600
The monkeys carried them up into the sky, and 10 minutes later,

38:59.600 --> 39:05.920
the friends were once again at the big green door of the Emerald City.

39:15.680 --> 39:19.680
Chapter 5 The Old Man from Kansas

39:23.520 --> 39:26.640
The little green man opened the door.

39:27.600 --> 39:29.520
He gave them all glasses.

39:30.480 --> 39:34.640
Then, he took them through the city to the Wizard's house.

39:35.760 --> 39:44.640
There, in the long green room, the friends waited and waited and waited.

39:44.880 --> 39:52.720
After three hours, the scarecrow said, I'm tired of waiting.

39:53.840 --> 39:55.520
He called the green man.

39:56.320 --> 40:02.560
We want to see the Wizard now, or we're going to call the magic monkeys.

40:03.200 --> 40:05.360
Please tell the Wizard that.

40:07.280 --> 40:11.440
The green man went away to speak to the Wizard through the door.

40:11.680 --> 40:18.720
The Wizard knew about the magic monkeys, and he was very afraid of them.

40:19.600 --> 40:21.600
So, he said to the green man,

40:23.360 --> 40:28.960
these people can come and see me at 9 o'clock tomorrow morning.

40:31.120 --> 40:35.760
At 9 o'clock, the green man took the friends to the Wizard's room.

40:36.560 --> 40:42.640
They went in and looked all round, but they could not see anybody.

40:43.920 --> 40:49.040
Then, a voice said, I am the Wizard of Oz.

40:50.080 --> 40:54.640
Who are you, and what do you want?

40:56.160 --> 40:58.880
Where are you, asked Dorothy?

41:00.080 --> 41:04.640
I am everywhere, but you can't see me.

41:05.280 --> 41:12.480
Now, answer me, who are you, and what do you want?

41:15.200 --> 41:18.320
You know us all, said the scarecrow.

41:18.880 --> 41:23.840
You said to me, help Dorothy to kill the Witch of the West,

41:24.400 --> 41:26.800
and you can have some brains.

41:27.440 --> 41:32.400
Well, the Witch is dead, and now I want my brains.

41:33.360 --> 41:37.200
And I want my heart, said the tin man.

41:37.920 --> 41:42.640
And I want to be brave, said the cowardly lion.

41:43.440 --> 41:47.520
And I want to go home to Kansas, said Dorothy.

41:49.120 --> 41:52.480
Is the Witch truly dead?

41:53.360 --> 41:54.240
Asked the voice.

41:55.120 --> 41:56.880
Yes, said Dorothy.

41:57.440 --> 42:01.280
I threw a bucket of water over her, and she disappeared.

42:02.160 --> 42:04.960
Very well, said the voice.

42:05.760 --> 42:07.680
Come again tomorrow.

42:08.480 --> 42:11.760
I must think about things first, and...

42:12.720 --> 42:14.880
No, said the tin man.

42:15.520 --> 42:17.680
I want my heart now.

42:19.120 --> 42:23.360
I'm not going to wait another minute, said the scarecrow.

42:24.160 --> 42:28.560
And I'm going to eat you, the lion shouted very angrily.

42:29.120 --> 42:30.320
Toto was afraid.

42:31.040 --> 42:35.760
He jumped away from the lion, and hid a scream near the wall.

42:36.800 --> 42:38.480
The scream fell over.

42:39.280 --> 42:44.160
And behind it, the friend saw an old man with no hair.

42:45.840 --> 42:49.440
The tin man looked angry and picked up his axe.

42:51.040 --> 42:53.120
Who are you, he said?

42:54.640 --> 42:56.400
Please, don't hurt me.

42:57.360 --> 43:00.160
Said the old man in a quiet little voice.

43:01.280 --> 43:03.200
I'm the Wizard of Oz.

43:04.880 --> 43:11.840
But the Wizard of Oz is a big head without a body, said Dorothy.

43:12.880 --> 43:17.360
No, she's a beautiful woman, said the scarecrow.

43:18.320 --> 43:20.960
You're wrong, said the tin man.

43:21.840 --> 43:27.120
The Wizard of Oz is a big animal with two heads.

43:28.800 --> 43:31.200
No, said the lion.

43:31.200 --> 43:34.080
The Wizard is a ball of fire.

43:36.000 --> 43:38.800
You're all wrong, said the old man.

43:39.760 --> 43:41.360
I am the Wizard.

43:42.320 --> 43:44.640
Well, I'm not a true Wizard.

43:45.760 --> 43:50.480
Oh, I know a lot of tricks, but I don't know any true magic.

43:51.520 --> 43:54.560
You see, I'm from Kansas too.

43:55.600 --> 43:59.280
I went from town to town and did magic tricks.

44:00.400 --> 44:02.800
And I went up in a big balloon.

44:03.920 --> 44:06.320
The balloon was always on a rope.

44:07.360 --> 44:09.680
But one day, something went wrong.

44:10.640 --> 44:13.840
The rope broke, and the balloon blew away.

44:15.120 --> 44:19.280
For a long time, the wind carried my balloon across the sky.

44:20.160 --> 44:24.400
Then, I came down here, in the country of Oz.

44:25.920 --> 44:28.240
The people saw my balloon and said,

44:28.960 --> 44:30.400
this man is a Wizard.

44:30.960 --> 44:32.320
He comes out of the sky.

44:33.840 --> 44:37.040
They were afraid of me and wanted to work for me.

44:38.000 --> 44:43.840
So, they built this city for me, and I called it the Emerald City.

44:44.640 --> 44:51.280
Well, Emeralds are green, so I made green glasses for everybody.

44:52.080 --> 44:55.120
That's why everything in the city looks green.

44:57.040 --> 44:59.360
The scarecrow took off his glasses.

45:00.400 --> 45:03.840
Oh, he said, now I understand.

45:04.640 --> 45:08.960
The Emerald City isn't green, it just looks green.

45:09.840 --> 45:10.800
It's all a trick.

45:12.320 --> 45:13.040
That's right.

45:13.840 --> 45:14.720
Said the old man.

45:15.920 --> 45:19.680
Well, all that happened many years ago.

45:20.960 --> 45:25.040
I never went out because I was afraid of the two bad witches.

45:26.160 --> 45:29.040
Now they are dead, thanks to you, Dorothy.

45:30.160 --> 45:31.360
But I'm very sorry.

45:32.160 --> 45:36.320
I don't know any true magic, so I can't help you.

45:38.240 --> 45:41.520
You're a very bad man, said Dorothy.

45:42.480 --> 45:43.680
No, my child.

45:44.480 --> 45:49.280
I'm a very good man, but I am a very bad wizard.

45:49.280 --> 45:49.920
That's true.

45:51.200 --> 45:54.480
What about my brains, said the scarecrow?

45:55.680 --> 45:57.200
You don't need brains.

45:58.000 --> 46:00.400
You understand things, you can think.

46:01.040 --> 46:03.760
You learn quickly, you're very clever.

46:04.960 --> 46:08.160
I want brains, said the scarecrow.

46:09.120 --> 46:11.920
Very well, said the old man.

46:12.560 --> 46:15.120
I can give you some brains tomorrow morning.

46:16.560 --> 46:18.080
What about my heart?

46:19.120 --> 46:20.160
Ask the tin man.

46:21.040 --> 46:24.080
You don't need a heart, said the old man.

46:24.880 --> 46:29.920
You laugh, you cry, you love, you feel sorry for people.

46:30.960 --> 46:34.560
The tin man looked angry and picked up his axe.

46:35.520 --> 46:39.840
All right, please don't hurt me, said the old man.

46:40.400 --> 46:43.120
I can give you a heart tomorrow morning.

46:44.560 --> 46:49.120
I want to be brave, said the cowardly lion.

46:50.320 --> 46:54.560
But you are brave, you do a lot of brave things.

46:55.600 --> 46:57.760
No, no, don't eat me.

46:58.480 --> 47:02.960
Come here tomorrow morning, I'm going to make you brave.

47:04.560 --> 47:07.440
What about Toto and me, asked Dorothy.

47:08.480 --> 47:11.600
We can go up in my balloon, said the wizard.

47:12.560 --> 47:14.880
The wind blew us here from Kansas.

47:15.520 --> 47:18.800
Perhaps it can blow us back to Kansas again.

47:21.280 --> 47:25.280
The next morning, the friends came again to the wizard's room.

47:26.000 --> 47:27.440
The old man was ready.

47:28.160 --> 47:32.560
He took a bottle with brains on it in big green letters

47:33.200 --> 47:36.080
and carefully opened the scarecrow's head.

47:37.200 --> 47:40.640
Don't move, I'm putting your brains in, he said.

47:41.600 --> 47:45.360
There, now you're the cleverest scarecrow in Oz.

47:46.400 --> 47:47.680
The scarecrow thanked him.

47:49.200 --> 47:54.480
Next, the wizard gave the tin man a small red heart.

47:56.080 --> 47:58.560
Where this always, he said,

47:59.520 --> 48:04.880
the tin man was very happy and thanked the wizard again and again.

48:06.480 --> 48:11.840
Then, the old man took a bottle with be brave on it.

48:12.800 --> 48:18.320
Drink this, he said to the cowardly lion, the lion drank.

48:19.360 --> 48:22.880
Yes, yes, I feel brave.

48:23.440 --> 48:27.760
He shouted, very, very brave, thank you.

48:29.520 --> 48:31.440
The wizard smiled at them.

48:32.720 --> 48:35.440
You didn't need my magic, he said.

48:36.160 --> 48:39.200
But you're all happy now, and that's a good thing.

48:40.000 --> 48:44.240
Now, Dorothy, he said, come and see my balloon.

48:44.960 --> 48:47.840
It's all ready, I mended it last night.

48:50.240 --> 48:53.360
They went out into the garden behind the wizard's house.

48:54.320 --> 48:56.160
The balloon was very big.

48:57.120 --> 49:02.320
There was a small box under it, and the wizard of Oz jumped into the box.

49:03.280 --> 49:04.480
Come on, Dorothy.

49:05.200 --> 49:07.920
He shouted, we're going to Kansas.

49:08.560 --> 49:10.240
Say goodbye to your friends.

49:12.080 --> 49:17.520
Dorothy kissed the scarecrow, the lion, and the tin man and said goodbye.

49:18.240 --> 49:22.880
Come on, Toto, she said, we're going home to Kansas.

49:22.880 --> 49:25.440
We're going to see Aunt Anne and Uncle Henry.

49:26.640 --> 49:29.760
But just then, Toto saw a cat.

49:30.480 --> 49:34.160
He jumped out of Dorothy's arms and ran after it.

49:34.960 --> 49:42.080
Toto called Dorothy, and she began to run after him.

49:42.880 --> 49:53.520
Chapter 6, Eve West Holmes Beth.

49:57.600 --> 50:01.680
Leave the dog and come quickly, shouted the wizard.

50:01.680 --> 50:03.040
The rope's going to break.

50:04.480 --> 50:06.560
Dorothy picked Toto up and ran.

50:07.280 --> 50:08.880
Wait, she shouted.

50:09.680 --> 50:13.360
But before she got there, the rope did break,

50:13.920 --> 50:18.640
and the balloon went up, up, up into the sky.

50:19.920 --> 50:23.600
They heard the old man's voice very far away.

50:24.720 --> 50:28.160
Ask the witch of the south.

50:30.320 --> 50:36.720
Then the balloon disappeared, and nobody saw the wizard of Oz again.

50:37.600 --> 50:39.760
Dorothy began to cry.

50:40.800 --> 50:44.000
Oh, how can I get home now?

50:45.040 --> 50:48.880
Put on the magic black hat, said the scarecrow,

50:48.880 --> 50:52.080
and asked the magic monkeys for help.

50:52.080 --> 50:57.040
Perhaps they can find the witch of the south and bring her here.

50:58.000 --> 51:01.280
Clever scarecrow, said Dorothy.

51:01.280 --> 51:06.640
She put on the magic hat and called for the magic monkey.

51:07.600 --> 51:10.000
When they arrived, she said,

51:10.000 --> 51:16.800
please, find the witch of the south and bring her here to the Emerald City.

51:18.080 --> 51:25.520
And five minutes later, a beautiful woman with long red hair arrived.

51:26.800 --> 51:30.960
I am Glinda, the witch of the south.

51:30.960 --> 51:35.920
She said, what can I do for you, my child?

51:37.520 --> 51:41.520
I want to go home to Kansas, said Dorothy.

51:42.160 --> 51:44.240
Please, can you help me?

51:45.520 --> 51:49.120
Ask your shoes, smiled the good witch,

51:50.000 --> 51:52.080
but Dorothy did not understand.

51:52.960 --> 51:57.920
Your red shoes, said Glinda, are magic shoes.

51:58.640 --> 52:00.320
They can carry you home.

52:01.120 --> 52:03.280
Just close your eyes and say,

52:04.160 --> 52:08.560
East, West, Home, Fest, then jump.

52:10.000 --> 52:13.280
Oh, thank you, cried Dorothy happily.

52:14.240 --> 52:17.120
She kissed her friends and said goodbye again.

52:18.000 --> 52:21.840
Then she picked up Toto and closed her eyes.

52:22.960 --> 52:27.840
East, West, Home, Fest, she said, and jumped.

52:28.800 --> 52:34.320
There was a noise like a wind, and suddenly, Dorothy was in the sky.

52:35.120 --> 52:40.000
The red shoes fell off her feet, and she never saw them again.

52:41.200 --> 52:47.520
When she opened her eyes, there she was, back in Kansas,

52:48.240 --> 52:54.720
and there were Antem and Uncle Henry in a field by a new little house.

52:55.680 --> 52:58.320
Dorothy, cried Antem.

52:58.880 --> 53:01.840
She ran and took Dorothy in her arms.

53:02.480 --> 53:07.520
Oh, Dorothy, what happened to you, and where did you come from?

53:08.800 --> 53:14.640
From the country of Oz, said Dorothy, but I'm home again now,

53:15.200 --> 53:17.120
and I'm so happy.

